.TH TOP 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
top \- display process information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B top
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B top
displays information about running processes and threads in the system.
The information is printed once to standard output and the program exits.
.PP
For each process/thread, the following information may be displayed:
.IP \(bu 3
Process ID (PID)
.IP \(bu
Thread ID (TID)
.IP \(bu
Process state
.IP \(bu
Parent process ID
.IP \(bu
Command name
.IP \(bu
CPU usage statistics
.SH NOTES
Unlike traditional Unix
.BR top ,
this command does not provide an interactive display that updates
periodically. It simply prints the current process list once and exits.
.PP
The output format and level of detail is controlled by the kernel's
.BR top (2)
system call.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR top (2),
.BR procstate (2),
.BR getpid (2)
